Sexual abuse committed by kids on other kids often goes unreported or dismissed by adults. This is brought about by fear of the consequences that this act has for the child offender and the one victimised. Any sexual act initiated by one person against another without that person’s consent is abuse. The act may be done with physical force, coercion, abuse of authority or against a person who is unable to give consent. Signs to look out for in your child: It is difficult to address this issue as it is difficult for adults to think of children as capable of sexually abusing others. Help your child by teaching the four ‘Rs: Prevention by means of educating children from a young age promotes healthy sexual behaviour from the onset. #plzcallme 083 323 1023 or email:mizzb@lovelife.org.za or Facebook: loveLifeNGO